HEADWORD: Comparator
<hw>Com"pa*ra`tor</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a
comparer.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An instrument or machine for
comparing anything to be measured with a standard measure; -- applied
especially to a machine for comparing standards of length.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

